'37:13': [
{sup:1, word:"send", lines:["Joseph&rsquo;s life was a copy of the life of Christ: in his being a shepherd ({Gen37:2|v. 2}; {Joh10:11|John 10:11}-{Joh10:16|16}); in his being his father&rsquo;s beloved (vv. {Gen37:3|3}-{Gen37:4|4}; {Mat3:17|Matt. 3:17}; {Mat17:5|17:5}); in his being sent by his father to minister to his brothers according to his father&rsquo;s will (vv. {Gen37:12|12}-{Gen37:17|17}; {Joh6:38|John 6:38}); in his being hated, persecuted, and betrayed (sold) by his brothers (vv. {Gen37:5|5}, {Gen37:18|18}-{Gen37:36|36}; {Joh15:25|John 15:25}; {Mat26:4|Matt. 26:4}, {Mat26:14|14}-{Mat26:16|16}); in his being cast into the prison of death with two criminals, one of whom was restored and the other executed ({Gen39:20|39:20}; {Gen40:1|40:1}-{Gen40:23|23}; {Act2:23|Acts 2:23}; {Luk23:32|Luke 23:32}, {Luk23:39|39}-{Luk23:43|43}); in his being released (resurrected) from the prison of death ({Gen41:14|41:14}; {Act2:24|Acts 2:24}); in his being enthroned with authority ({Gen41:40|41:40}-{Gen41:44|44}; {Mat28:18|Matt. 28:18}; {Act2:36|Acts 2:36}; {Rev3:21|Rev. 3:21}); in his receiving glory and gifts ({Gen41:42|41:42}; {Heb2:9|Heb. 2:9}; {Psa68:18|Psa. 68:18}; {Act2:33|Acts 2:33}); in his becoming the savior of the world, the sustainer of life (the revealer of secrets) ({Gen41:45|41:45} and {Gen41:45^1|note 1}; {Act5:31|Acts 5:31}; {Joh6:50|John 6:50}-{Joh6:51|51}); in his taking a wife from the Gentiles ({Gen41:45|41:45}; {Joh3:29|John 3:29}; {Eph5:23|Eph. 5:23}-{Eph5:27|27}; {Rev19:7|Rev. 19:7}; cf. {Mat1:1^4|note 1<sup>4</sup>} in {Mat1|Matt. 1}); in his supplying people with food ({Gen41:56|41:56}-{Gen41:57|57}; {Joh6:35|John 6:35}); in his acknowledging his ignorant brothers and being recognized by them ({Gen45:1|45:1}-{Gen45:4|4}, {Gen45:14|14}-{Gen45:15|15}; {Rom11:26|Rom. 11:26}; {Zec12:10|Zech. 12:10}; {Rev1:7|Rev. 1:7}); and in his reigning in the kingdom over the whole earth ({Gen41:40|41:40}&mdash;{Gen50:26|50:26}; {Rev11:15|Rev. 11:15}; {Dan7:13|Dan. 7:13}-{Dan7:14|14})."]},
],
