'39:12': [
{sup:"1a", word:"fled", vrefs:"1&nbsp;Cor. 6:18; 2&nbsp;Tim. 2:22", lines:["Joseph lived a life that corresponded to the vision he saw in his two dreams (see {Gen37:5^1|note 5<sup>1</sup>} in {Gen37|ch. 37}; cf. {Act26:19|Acts 26:19}). Joseph&rsquo;s brothers vented their anger ({Gen37:18|37:18}-{Gen37:31|31}) and indulged in their lust ({Gen38:15|38:15}-{Gen38:18|18}), but Joseph subdued his anger and conquered his lust, behaving as a sheaf full of life and conducting himself like a heavenly star shining in the darkness (see notes {Gen37:18^1|18<sup>1</sup>} in {Gen37|ch. 37} and {Gen38:15^1|15<sup>1</sup>} in {Gen38|ch. 38}). Joseph&rsquo;s life under the heavenly vision was the life of the kingdom of the heavens described in {Mat5|Matt. 5}&mdash;{Mat7|7}. By living such a life, he was fully prepared to reign as a king."]},
],
